text: .. UP Election Result Are you eagerly waiting for the UP Election Result ? Check the latest Assembly Election Predictions Updates and Opinion Polls here on this single page. Elections of Uttar Pradesh were held from February 11, 2017 to March 8 2017. On the opinion of the exit poll, India Today spoke to political experts and pundits to get their predictions about the Uttar Pradesh election outcome. This year, lots of mind games and plotting are taking into consider. The Samajwadi Party coordinates with the Congress and entered into a seat where as the BJP which is on top with the charisma of Prime Minister Narendra Modi make the results on fire. Assembly Constituencies have 403 total seats and for achieving the UP Election 202 seats are required by the candidates to acquire. The elections were held in seven phases commencing on February 11, the first phase. The second phase voting was held on February 15, third phase voting took place on February 19. Voting for the fourth and fifth phase was held on February 23 and February 27 respectively. Sixth and seventh phase voting took place on March 4 and March 8 respectively. The outcome of UP Elections will be schedule on 11 March 2017.
